                            <comment id="34399" author="bobijam" created="Tue, 10 Apr 2012 10:49:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;dup of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1270&quot; title=&quot;lfs find -size returns &amp;quot;obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1270&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1270&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="32885" author="bobijam" created="Fri, 30 Mar 2012 01:36:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;2.2 client has &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1270&quot; title=&quot;lfs find -size returns &amp;quot;obd_uuid: (null) failed No such device&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1270&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1270&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="32317" author="sarah" created="Wed, 28 Mar 2012 14:38:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hit the similar error in 2.2RC2 testing. Server: 2.1.1-RHEL6-x86_64  Client: 2.2RC2-RHEL6-x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a53354ce-78f3-11e1-8f60-5254004bbbd3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a53354ce-78f3-11e1-8f60-5254004bbbd3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14928" author="bobijam" created="Mon, 23 May 2011 18:19:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;dup of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-274&quot; title=&quot;Client delayed file status (cache meta-data) causing job failures&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-274&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-274&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14713" author="bobijam" created="Fri, 20 May 2011 01:51:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-274&quot; title=&quot;Client delayed file status (cache meta-data) causing job failures&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-274&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-274&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;background: sanity 56r is to test &apos;lfs -find&apos; function, it creates 4 dirs, and each contains 3 empty files, and create another file (named &apos;56r&apos;) which contains 5 chars in it. The failed test is &apos;lfs find -size 5&apos; which is supposed to got the &apos;56r&apos; while test result found none.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;from the debug log, the 56r was created and 5 chars are written:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(namei.c:525:ll_lookup_it()) VFS Op:name=56r,dir=144115205255839738/33554436(ffff8103190b1b50),intent=open|creat&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
(namei.c:591:ll_lookup_it()) Process leaving via out (rc=0 : 0 : 0x0)&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
(namei.c:781:ll_create_it()) VFS Op:name=56r,dir=144115205255839738/33554436(ffff8103190b1b50),intent=open|creat&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
(namei.c:800:ll_create_it()) Process leaving (rc=0 : 0 : 0)&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
(file.c:1075:ll_file_write()) Process entered&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
(file.c:1087:ll_file_write()) Process leaving (rc=5 : 5 : 5)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for some reason, &apos;lfs -find&apos; does not get the correct file size of &apos;56r&apos; and failed the test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14492" author="pjones" created="Wed, 18 May 2011 07:31:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bobijam&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into this test failure?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
